For Temporal.Date, the offset is actually optional, so we don't always want to throw an exception here.  Essentially the logic should be:

Try to parse as a Date with an offset.
If that fails, try to parse as a Date with no offset.
If that fails too, throw an exception.

So the code should look something like:
try {
    OffsetDateTime odt = OffsetDateTime.parse(text, getOffsetDateTimeFormatter());
    localDate = LocalDate.from(odt);
    zoneOffset = ZoneOffset.from(odt);
} catch (DateTimeParseException exception) {
    try {
        // Optional timezone offset not present
        localDate = LocalDate.parse(text, DateTimeFormatter.ISO_LOCAL_DATE);
        zoneOffset = null;
    } catch (DateTimeParseException exception) {
        throw new IllegalArgumentException("Failed to create Temporal.Date object from " + text, exception);
    }
}

Please also add similar logic in the Temporal.Time class as well!

